{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "While some methods have been evaluated only on small Transformer-based language models [102], others have been tested on earlier LLMs such as GPT-2 [23].",
    "The performance of these methods (e.g., [98,102]) on the latest LLMs, such as Llama-3 and GPT-4, still requires in-depth evaluation.",
    "Moreover, some of these methods may not perform well in the presence of defense mechanisms such as differential privacy (DP) [2].",
    "Therefore, further research is needed to develop attack methods that address the aforementioned issues in PII leakage attacks against LLMs.",
    "As LLMs become integral components in applications ranging from NLP to multi-modal systems, the vulnerabilities associated with their usage pose serious concerns."
  ],
